@startuml posterior-fusion
' Neural emission posteriors fused into the WFST decoding graph.
' AcousticModel::forward emits per-frame log-posteriors P(unit∣frame); FusionConfig
' weights them against the LM score inside the recognition network N = H∘C∘L∘G;
' the weighted product is searched (Viterbi/beam) to yield words.
' Matches AcousticModel / FusionConfig / AcousticLanguageModel in src/acoustic/mod.rs.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #6A1B9A
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.4
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
  FontColor #102027
  BorderColor #E65100
}

title <b>Neural posterior fusion into the decoding graph</b>\n<size:11><latex>\text{combined} = \lambda_{am} \cdot \log P(\text{unit} \mid \text{frame}) + \lambda_{lm} \cdot \log P(\text{word} \mid \text{context}) + \text{penalties}</latex></size>

rectangle "<b>Audio frames</b>\n[<latex>T \times</latex> feature_dim]" as X #ECEFF1
rectangle "<b>AcousticModel</b>\nneural net · forward()" as AM #E1BEE7
rectangle "<b>Posteriors</b>\n<latex>\log P(\text{unit} \mid \text{frame})</latex>\nFramePosterior / PosteriorSequence" as POST #E1BEE7

X  -down-> AM  : features
AM -down-> POST : per-frame log-probs

rectangle "<b>Recognition network N</b>\n<latex>H \circ C \circ L \circ G</latex>   (unit → word)" as N #FFB74D
rectangle "<b>FusionConfig</b>\n<latex>\lambda_{am}</latex> · acoustic_weight\n<latex>\lambda_{lm}</latex> · lm_weight\nword/blank penalties" as FUSE #FFE0B2

POST -down-> FUSE : <latex>\lambda_{am} \cdot \log P(\text{unit} \mid \text{frame})</latex>
N    -down-> FUSE : <latex>\lambda_{lm} \cdot \log P(\text{word} \mid \text{context})</latex>

rectangle "<b>Search</b>\nViterbi / beam over  <latex>\text{posteriors} \otimes N</latex>" as DEC #C8E6C9
rectangle "<b>Words</b>" as W #ECEFF1

FUSE -down-> DEC : weighted product
DEC  -down-> W

note right of FUSE
  Scores live in a log-domain semiring (LogWeight), so
  the fused product is a semiring <latex>\otimes</latex> and alternative paths
  combine with <latex>\oplus</latex>. AcousticLanguageModel::to_log_weight
  packages the result as a WFST arc weight.
end note
@enduml
